<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1451,1720,2035]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,291,1792,1818]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">Habitat:</emphasis>
—This taxon was found associated with periphyton of 
<taxonomicName box="[894,1104,1792,1818]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lentibulariaceae" genus="Utricularia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="foliosa">
<emphasis box="[894,1104,1792,1818]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">Utricularia foliosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. EC 0.07 (± 0.03 mS 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1341,1389,1792,1819]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">cm-1</superScript>
), 
<collectionCode box="[1411,1451,1792,1818]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14073" name="Société d'Agriculture Sciences et Arts" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" type="Herbarium">DO</collectionCode>
6.6 (± 
<quantity box="[210,288,1828,1855]" metricMagnitude="-7" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" unit="mg" value="0.3">0.3 mg</quantity>
L- 
<superScript attach="right" box="[318,325,1828,1842]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">1</superScript>
), pH 6.6 (± 0.6), TDS 0.03 (± 0.01), 
<collectionCode box="[741,758,1829,1855]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">T</collectionCode>
27.6 (± 0.2 ºC), WT 0.7 (± 
<quantity box="[1068,1150,1828,1855]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" unit="m" value="0.14">0.14 m</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1451,1720,2035]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,245,1864,1890]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">Note</emphasis>
:—This species was originally described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lacoste de Diaz, E. N." box="[742,1004,1864,1891]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292" pagination="203 - 223" refId="ref5049" refString="Lacoste de Diaz, E. N. (1972) Nota sobre las Desmidiaceae de la region de Valinhos (Sao Paulo, Brasil). Boletin de la Sociedad Argentina de Botanica 14 (3): 203 - 223." type="journal article" year="1972">Lacoste de Díaz (1972)</bibRefCitation>
based on samples gathered in Valinhos, 
<collectingRegion box="[136,253,1900,1926]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, Southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[417,489,1900,1926]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. This was the only record of this species till now. Almost 50 years later, it was found again in 
<collectingCountry box="[232,303,1936,1962]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, but now in 
<collectingRegion box="[442,510,1936,1962]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, Northeast region.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1451,1720,2035]" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">
The cell outline (7–8 angled), as well as wide and straight apices are the main morphological features of this species. The SEM analysis revealed that the cell wall is slightly scrobiculate (pock marked pattern) (
<figureCitation box="[1261,1345,2008,2035]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–32" captionStartId="3.[136,243,1729,1751]" captionTargetBox="[175,1415,192,1698]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[159,1428,187,1707]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 9–32. LM and SEM. 9–15. Cosmarium boeckii var. areolatum: LM (9–12), SEM (15), frontal view (9, 10, 15), lateral view (11, 12), apical view (13, 14), 16–21. C. clepsydra var. incrassatum: frontal view (16–19), lateral view (20), apical view (21), 22–26. C. heptangulare: LM (22–25), SEM (26), frontal view (22–23, 26), lateral view (24), apical view (25), 27–32. C. kanetsunae: frontal view (27–28), lateral view (29, 30), apical view (31, 32). Scale bar: 10 μm, except Fig. 15 (5 μm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5421000" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5421000/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="292">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,158,256]" pageId="2" pageNumber="293">
Another feature which we consider relevant in this species is the apical view, which is oblong. Somewhat similar species such as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Borge 1913: 19)" baseAuthorityName="Borge" baseAuthorityPageNumber="19" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[314,780,194,221]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Cosmarium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="2" pageNumber="293" phylum="Charophyta" rank="species" species="lapponicum">
<emphasis box="[314,584,194,221]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="293">Cosmarium lapponicum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Borge, O." box="[600,772,194,220]" pageId="2" pageNumber="293" pagination="97 - 110" refId="ref4593" refString="Borge, O. (1913) Beitrage zur Algenflora von Schweden, II. Die Algenflora um den Torne-Trask-see in Schwedisch-Lappland. Botaniska Notiser 1913: 1 - 32, 49 - 64, 97 - 110." type="journal article" year="1913">Borge 1913:19</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Nordstedt (Wittrock &amp; Nordstedt 1878: 71)" authorityName="Nordstedt (Wittrock &amp; Nordstedt" authorityYear="1878" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Cosmarium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="2" pageNumber="293" phylum="Charophyta" rank="species" species="fontigenum">
<emphasis box="[840,1000,194,221]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="293">C. fontigenum</emphasis>
Nordstedt (
<bibRefCitation author="Wittrock, V. B. &amp; Nordstedt, O." pageId="2" pageNumber="293" pagination="67 - 73" refId="ref5700" refString="Wittrock, V. B. &amp; Nordstedt, O. (1878) Algae aquae dulcis exsiccatae praecipue Scandinavicae quas adjectis algis marinis chlorophyllaceis et phycochromaceis distribuerunt. Botaniska Notiser 1878: 67 - 73." type="journal article" year="1878">Wittrock &amp; Nordstedt 1878: 71</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
have elliptical cells when observed in apical view.
</paragraph>
